HEADWORD: Impletion
<hw>Im*ple"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impletio</ets>. See <er>Implement</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of filling, or the state of being full.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which fills up; filling.</def>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Implex</ent>⟦br⟧
